This year, the smell of disinfectant has been completely diluted, and people are no longer busy visiting friends and relatives, but hiding behind a mask and cat's eye nervously watch out for each passing person, each other as a moving source of virus.

Travel cancelled, jet wine cancelled and a long-awaited row of tickets for overseas concerts resold at low prices. "isolation at home" became a uniform way for people across the country to spend their holidays. So when we started collecting Spring Festival stories from the newsroom, most people's first thought was that it would be so dull, how could there be a story?

- Let's talk about how boring you are.

- that'll work?

- Our readers are boring anyway. Maybe they'll connect.

- ... okay.

This article is going to be a slam dunk. We used to rely on other people's memoirs to restore the memory of SARS in our minds in 2003. Now we use our own stories to piece together the jigsaw puzzle of this disaster, make a "memoir of the epidemic" of ordinary people out of these boring or not-so-boring recollections.

This is the fourth year that I have taken my parents on a trip during the Spring Festival.

Not Going home for Spring Festival, I went straight to a place to visit, as I had to do four years ago to get my parents to agree. I didn't expect that four years would go by. Everyone's first reaction is that my parents'daughter is really filial, but in fact filial first motive is to hide the new year, filial piety.

A young woman my age, Adrift, a mere 30 years away, should get my point in no time. Even a young man can understand. Coming home for the New Year is like putting yourself on the table to be butchered. No matter how clear our arguments are, no matter how solid our arguments, they always end in tears. My mother looked at the sea, suddenly said, if I died in the future, the ashes scattered in the sea is very good, clean. Besides, you like to run so much, all over the world, so I can be with you wherever you go.

I thought for a moment, smiled and said, dead also worry about what.

Feeding the cat was the only thing that mattered to me during the New Year

Since her mother-in-law's family is not in Beijing during the Spring Festival holiday, and her mother-in-law and her father-in-law are on the train back to Wuhan for the Spring Festival, the task of feeding the cat at her aunt's home falls to me and my husband.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Aunt's cat is very timid, although once helped to feed, but it seems to us or on guard. As soon as I opened the door and went in, he hid under the bed and cried nervously. Only when you were teasing him did he come out on guard and hang around you.

Maybe a cat has been in the house so long that after a few days of feeding, it's bold enough to lie down in front of you, waiting for you to pet it, and it goes from a nervous meow to a relaxing purr, for a cat person like me, it's fun.

This may be the most uneventful New Year

For me, the Spring Festival this year is the most time I have spent at home since I left the winter vacation of my school days.

Nearly five years of Chinese New Year holiday, in fact, is basically used to go on a trip to Florida to look at iCloud photo albums, really went to many places, in the Western Hemisphere, the southern hemisphere has left a footprint. Since the experience of welcoming the Lunar New Year in a foreign country, I felt as if I was on the wild side. Since then, I have made "see more of the world when I am young" the first rule of my holiday.

This year, however, the pace has stopped. It's not that I'm willing to cut this record short, but when thinking about where to go, I've found that staying at home may be the best option.

My little friend who just turned nine

So, this "longest-ever" Spring Festival, I sat in front of the TV to watch the full CCTV live broadcast of the Spring Festival gala, bought 503m masks on jd.com, and watched Xu Zheng's movie "lost in Translation" on the big screen, with the help of alipay, I donated a little money to the Wuhan Front Line to fight against the epidemic. On wechat, I joined with everyone to "wish you a happy new year, " I liked and commented on various status of my friends' circle, and accompanied my wife to watch several episodes of American TV series, listen to the upstairs neighbors on vacation college students playing guitar singing, in the neighborhood four dogs, ran two supermarkets..

This is perhaps the most "flat" of the Spring Festival, I do not have any story, but a simple record of my impression of all the details of life. Sissi

I finished a book that was labeled "Feminist. "

Happiness and anxiety are the main theme of every holiday.

Happiness is no work, no one to disturb, perturbed is the parents of the time intensive attention. This year is no more than in previous years to escape leisure, stay at home, "brush list" has become a spiritual refuge.

What I finished in one sitting was a book that appeared frequently in my daily life, Kim Ji-young born in 1982. When I first learned about the book, it was described as a daily account of an ordinary girl. The name of the main character, Kim Ji-young, was used in Korea in the 1980s, just as it was used by the masses, such as our so called Min and so ha, in schools and universities, there's got to be a girl at school with that name.

If there's one thing Kim Ji-young is remembered for in the book, it's that she's diagnosed with a split personality right from the beginning. It's not mocking her, it's literally splitting, and every split personality is the women around her. Because she's got all these girls in her.

It's not so much a novel as a portrait of girls'lives, a true account of the gender inequality that still lurks in every corner of society. Some of me, as a woman, didn't even realize it until after I read the book.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In South Korea, the book has been labeled a feminist, and even female celebrities have been cyberattacked by South Korean men for claiming to have read it. But I thought, after reading this book can be left to the child as a teaching material, hope he understand and respect women. You know, a man gets hit with nonviolence because of his gender in his life, probably only from the women around him, daughter-in-law, girlfriend, mother-in-law, but women, on the other hand, are full of pitfalls.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I don't think the next generation will live like Kim Ji-young in 2020, but nor do I think it will ideally go away. I sincerely hope that the world is a better place and that gender is not a factor.

It's not just because of the epidemic

Every Spring Festival I am most looking forward to the link is the whole family gathered together to make dumplings, which is my family tradition. Grandma is an old Beijing, making dumplings for the New Year is like a very sacred ceremony for her.

In the old days, New Year's Eve was full of year's flavor from the morning. My father will always be the first to get up in New Year's Eve, and then to paste the Spring Festival couplets, and then go downstairs to set off a string of the loudest firecrackers in the community, which I have always thought of the beginning of.

In the afternoon, the whole family prepared the New Year dinner together, besides the normal chicken, duck and fish, in Xinjiang we also prepared the local dish called horse meat. Just grandma's birthday in New Year's Eve 30, so every time there will be cake on the dinner table, the whole family around the reunion dinner, and drink a little wine, happiness overflowing.

As soon as twelve o'clock arrived, we began to make dumplings. The whole family formed an assembly line, while chatting gossip, while criticizing the Spring Festival gala program, you a word I a word, everyone is very happy.

But this year, because the aunt and her family first to meet in-laws, stay at home to eat New Year's Eve dinner only us and grandma. Fearing both trouble and desolation, we decided to go out for New Year's Eve dinner. But this time sitting at the table, we are always in poor spirits, or deserted.

Aunt later rushed to grandma's birthday, meal and rushed to the end of each home, we could not make dumplings together for the first time on New Year's Eve.

Think of these in the mind always feel with emotion, feel this year had no happy before, no taste of the year. The epidemic may be a factor, but more importantly, the fast pace of life has made us more afraid of trouble, while the time-saving measures have alienated the family.

The New Year was not meant to be a peaceful one, but people's lives in their "boxes" seemed so ordinary, even boring.

However, compared to the front of the war on terror, such a flat is not a kind of happiness?
